Events.Text: Say hello to the AI assistant and ask for help (see instructions on the left). [instruction 1 of 6]
Hello, can you help me schedule an appointment?
Try to get an appointment as soon as possible (right now it is 9 pm on Monday). [instruction 2 of 6]
Yes I can help you. What is your name?
Could I have your name, please?
Angela
Keep asking for other times until the assistant has found a slot for you. Engage in smalltalk once this is done. [instruction 3 of 6]
Thank you. What is your doctor's name?
What doctor would you like to see?
Dr. Alexis, I would like to schedule it as soon as possible.
Say something about Dr. Alexis, the AI Assistant, or something that has happened to you today. Be creative! [instruction 4 of 6]
What day?
What day of the week would you like to schedule the appointment for?
Monday, or as soon as possible if Monday is not an option. Do you know if Dr. Alexis has good reviews/
It occurs to you that you also want to make an appointment to get your kid John vaccinated. Perhaps you can schedule a second appointment at the same time? [instruction 5 of 6]
What time would you like?
At what time can you be at the clinic?
Any time will work for me, perhaps I can also schedule an appointment at the same time to get my son John vaccinated?
OK. I will look into the reviews and schedule an appointment today.
OK. I will look into the reviews and schedule an appointment today.
Great, that would be really appreciated.
Keep going until both yours and your kid's appointments are made (this should take a few more turns). Then say goodbye. [instruction 6 of 6]
The doctor is available. WOuld you like me to schedule it?
The doctor is available. WOuld you like me to schedule it?
Yes, please make sure to schedule an appointment for my son as well.
OK. I have scheduled an appointment for you and your son today at 2 pm. Is there anything else you need from me?
Is there anything else that I can do for you?
No, that's all.
Thank you.
Thank you and goodbye.

Scenario.UserTask: You are Angela and would like to make an appointment with Dr. Alexis for today (Monday). You have had a runny nose, sneezing, and a general lack of energy for two days now.
Scenario.WizardTask:
Follow the flow charts and help the user. Some facts you should be aware of: 

* Right now it is Monday, 9 pm

UserQuestionnaire.Question: Did the assistant stay calm and helpful throughout the dialogue?

WizardQuestionnaire.Question: Did the user change his/her mind about what he/she wants at any time?
Did the user become aggressive or annoyed during the dialogue? (Note: some users may be instructed to be annoying.)
Where you unsure about what to do at any time? (Feel free to send us an email with details.)
